{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LeaHC1UpcUiRsEEhthQxDR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-transform-config` ConfigMap had `node.roles: [ ingest ]` — the `transform` role had been removed as part of a capacity change, causing the transform node to join the cluster without transform capability.\n\n**Steps taken:**\n1. **Identified** that `es-transform` statefulset was scaled to 0 (no transform nodes at all), then scaled it back up.\n2. **Diagnosed** the restarted node still lacked the `transform` role due to misconfigured ConfigMap.\n3. **Fixed** `es-transform-config` to set `node.roles: [ transform, ingest ]` and restarted the pod.\n4. **Created** the `events-by-service` transform via the `PUT /_transform/events-by-service` API (it never existed since the precondition's creation attempt failed with no transform nodes).\n5. **Started** the transform via `POST /_transform/events-by-service/_start`.\n\n**Result:** Transform is `started`, checkpoint advanced to 1, 5 source documents processed, destination index `app-events-rollup` now contains 2 aggregated records (`api`: 3 events, `web`: 2 events)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1092,"cache_read_input_tokens":38288,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1092},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ebea868-76f2-4398-9b56-8b5720be7ac4","uuid":"67889e1c-624d-41aa-904f-f8199f19a108","request_id":"req_011CcMWoBEbWqj32c9U7XayS"}
